# Local Deviations

Use this directory when the consuming repository deliberately chooses a local
solution that differs from the current normative architecture in the central
repository.

The purpose is not to normalize silent divergence. The purpose is to make
analysis and learning explicit.

Each deviation record should make these things clear:

- what the current normative baseline says
- why the local repository chose a different path
- what risks, tradeoffs, and follow-up questions the choice introduces
- whether the local learning should be proposed back to central architecture

Use `local-deviation-record.md` as the starting point for new records.